name: hypr Wien #1
description:
Hyprs are a collection of hyper-ornamental structures generated through lattice subdivision and other geometric operations. They draw inspiration from Art Nouveau, Art Deco and Vienna Secession movements, but interpret them through the lens of generative design. The collection is created by hyprloos, an alternate account of luka, and features exclusively high-resolution stills.
